The paper deals with the problem of fresh data collection in UAV-assisted IoT networks, which involves optimizing the flight trajectory of the UAV and transmission scheduling of the sensors to minimize the age of information. This problem is related to several sub-fields of computer science, including networked systems (cs.NI), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), control systems (cs.SY), and information theory (cs.IT). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper, ordered from most to least likely.
